defaultThe Civil Engineering Contractors Association (CECA) welcomes the opportunity to respond to the above named call for evidence. 
default&#xa0;
defaultCECA provides the voice for those companies who create, improve and maintain th
defaulte UK’s vital transport and utility networks. Our membership of more than 300 companies together delivers an estimated 70-80 per cent of all infrastructure construction work carried out nationwide. Our industry supports the employment of around 200,000 peop
defaultle with annual activity worth up to £25 billion.
default&#xa0;
defaultCECA cautiously welcomes the introduction of local decision making on transport expenditure. While there is a long way to go before the success of the policy can be measured, it is clear that greater integr
defaultation between bodies operating at local and regional level is required
default to enable effective delivery
default.  
default&#xa0;
defaultCECA is concerned that there is a lack of clarity as to how the funding will be allocated and how local bodies are expected to work together to deliver 
defaultmajor transport projects. We call on Government to work with all 
defaultbodies 
defaultinvolved in 
defaultthe 
defaultfuture delivery of 
defaultlocal transport 
defaultprojects to address this to ensure that any proposed developments are not burdened from the start by confusion.
default&#xa0;
defaultIn our response, we 
defaulthave focused on the areas in which we believe we can add the most value. We trust that you find our comments helpful and that they will be taken into consideration.
