default&#xa0;defaultRationaledefault&#xa0;
defaultThe 2010 Coalition Agreement clearly set out the current Government’s localist intentions and the Localism Act devolved decision making powers from central government to individuals, communities and councils.
default&#xa0;
defaultIn 2010 Local Enterprise Partnerships (LEPs) w
defaultere announced taking over the role of Regional Development Agencies in terms of promoting local economic growth.
